name: SystemIntegrationMP2-CamundaTasks
description: Microservice using RabbitMQ message broker to complete Camunda Tasks using CamundaAPI

name: SystemIntegrationMP2-CamundaExternalTasks
description: Microservice using RabbitMQ message broker to complete Camunda External Tasks using CamundaAPI

name: Microservices-Driven-Order-Management-System-with-Spring-and-Angular
description: This project is a microservices-based Order Management System using Spring and Angular. It includes services for orders, customers, inventory, a gateway, and utilizes Consul and Vault for service discovery and secure configuration. The Angular frontend allows customers to view orders and products.

name: ims
description: Inventory Management System built using springBoot microservices architecture.

name: System-Based-a-Microsservices-with-Serverless-Architecture
description: The main objective of this project is the study of microservices technologies and the implementation of a system based on microservices with serverless architecture for event management.

name: NotificationPreferenceService
description: Related to  Manning's Microservices Notification System Design. A notification preferences microservice with an API to retrieve a fictional customer's notification preference based on the customerId.

name: config-repo
description: The project is a Banking Management System using Microservices architecture, with Consul serving as the configuration repository.

name: opentelemetry-demo
description: This repository contains the OpenTelemetry Astronomy Shop, a microservice-based distributed system intended to illustrate the implementation of OpenTelemetry in a near real-world environment.

name: Medicure
description: Medicure: Spring Boot microservice with CI/CD using Git, Jenkins, Docker, Ansible, Selenium, Terraform, Kubernetes. Implements automated testing, deployment, and monitoring for a hospital management system.

name: food-ordering
description: Food ordering system application: Implement SAGA, Outbox and CQRS patterns using the 4 Spring boot Java microservices that you will develop using Clean and Hexagonal architecture principles and with DDD.

name: logauth
description: LogAuth features a login microservice system and sends confirmation emails for new sign-ups. The application uses Spring Boot’s security for OAuth and JMS for email functionality. Further enhancements are underway.
